  "original_title": "\u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1 \u0db4\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dc0\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca\u0dc4\u0dbd\u0dca 1,060 \u0d9a\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dca.\u0d86\u0dbb\u0dca. \u0d9a\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0db8\u0dba\u0da7 \u0dc3\u0dd6\u0daf\u0dcf\u0db1\u0db8\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "1,060 gas stations in Q.R. Method ready",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Q.R. of the National Fuel License. 1,060 gas stations had complied with the code as of last night (30) and 746 gas stations were Q.R. yesterday. Electricity and Energy Minister Kanchana Wijesekera said that fuel was released through the system.",
        "Of those 746 gas stations, 621 Cipetco stations and I.O.C. The minister mentioned that there are 125 filling stations where more than 21 lakh liters of fuel were given.",
        "At that time, the minister said that nearly 48 lakh vehicles were registered in the National Fuel License, including 2,784,762 motorcycles and 639,361 cars."
      ],
